Stink bugs!  These critters have been alarmingly increasing in number throughout BC. The rise of these bugs can be seen as a side effect of climate change, as climate change has altered their environment. As an invasive species not native to BC, these bugs can have devastating effects on our agricultural sector. They can also be a nuisance to homeowners.  The Government of British Columbia has published a Brown Marmorated Stink Bug (BMSB) Pest Alert, alerting residents to be cautious of this pest in their area. The government is asking residents to be careful in not moving these pests from one place to another as they are an invasive species. They are also collecting data on these bugs and are asking people to send samples of these bugs to them for research purposes. Below we have linked the pest alert issued by the Government of British Columbia, and a guide on how to properly handle and dispose these bugs for home owners. Pest Alert: https://www2.gov.bc.ca/gov/content/industry/agriculture-seafood/animals-and-crops/plant-health/insects-and-plant-diseases/tree-fruits/brown-marmorated-stink-bug Guide: https://www2.gov.bc.ca/assets/gov/farming-natural-resources-and-industry/agriculture-and-seafood/animal-and-crops/plant-health/stinkbug-_rackcard.pdf Have questions on Stink Bugs?
